    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <h2>Stuff &amp; Things</h2>
          <p>Our curated list of recent, suggested listening, reading and viewing.</p>
          <dl>
            <dt><a href="https://www.theverge.com/2022/3/15/22979126/vimeo-patreon-creators-price-increase">Vimeo is telling creators to suddenly pay thousands of dollars ...</a></dt>
            <dd>... or leave the platform. We&apos;ve long suggested that users host video content on Vimeo rather than YouTube, but I think that&apos;s going to have to change in light of this recent reporting from The Verge.</dd>
            
            <dt><a href="https://www.newyorker.com/culture/culture-desk/your-camera-roll-contains-a-masterpiece">Your Camera Roll Contains a Masterpiece</a></dt>
            <dd>From the Culture Desk of The New Yorker, a really lovely read about finding the masterpieces buried in your photo pile.</dd>
            
            <dt><a href="https://i-d.vice.com/en_uk/article/akvbwb/yakuza-women-photographs-chloe-jafe">Photographing the hidden lives of Yakuza women</a></dt>
            <dd>Chloé Jafé&apos;s series, <cite>I give you my life</cite>, lifts the veil on the secret lives of women in the Japanese mob. Follow <a href="https://www.instagram.com/chloe.jafe/">@chloe.jafe</a> on Instagram. <small>(content warning: nudity)</small></dd>
            
            <dt><a href="https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/12/23042995/black-hole-image-event-horizon-telescope-sagittarius-a-milky-way">... picture of the supermassive black hole at the heart of the Milky Way</a></dt>
            <dd>If you haven't seen this by now, it&apos;s very cool and worth seeing.</dd>
            
            <dt><a href="https://petapixel.com/2022/05/11/huge-grey-owl-lands-on-wildlife-photographers-camera/">Great Grey Owl Lands on Wildlife Photographer’s Camera</a></dt>
            <dd>This is a fun one, and there are some great images in here. And I may or may not be setting up a bird theme for later.</dd>

            <dt><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l94kK-S8wvc">Music Pick: "Patterns" by Stars</a></dt>
            <dd>A really lovely song and video from one of my favorite bands, Stars. So far, I'm lovely everything they've released from their upcoming album, and I am extremely excited A) to be seeing them in concert in June, and B) to be seeing a concert again after so long without them.</dd>
          </dl>
        </mj-text>        
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text>
          <p class="social-links">
